
            Video
            Timothy Spall plays Churchill at closing ceremony
            The closing ceremony of the London 2012 Games has got under way with some of the biggest names in British pop playing to 80,000 people at the Olympic Stadium.A spectacular cityscape in the shape of a union jack was unveiled. The actor Timothy Spall emerged from the top of a model of Big Ben as Winston Churchill and performed Caliban's speech from The Tempest.
                
                        16 Jan 2013
                    
                
        
